main event: A witness observed a star-like object that traveled across the sky and disappeared in the southeast, moving faster than a commercial aircraft.
interesting points: The object seemed to move faster than a commercial aircraft.
The description is consistent with that of an aircraft, with no unusual characteristics noted.
The observers did not believe the object to be an unusual or unidentified flying object.
The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes.
The witness compared the object to the ECHO balloon, but noted it was much larger, lower, and traveling at a much faster rate of speed.
